      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THE ART OF SUCCESS (3) continued her terrific progress and extended her winning run to five when she led and kept going to score by 4.7 metres at this venue last time. Draws low enough to push forward again so can add to the picket fence. Stalemate STORMS COLLIDE (7) looks the danger. Draws wide and hasn't raced since the Vicbred final in November but he flies fresh with three wins and a placing from four attempts and he should be ready to go again after two nice trials. SOAP AND BUBBLES (1) continued her consistent form when she won at this circuit and distance two back before a second from much wider last week. The ace draw should see her make an impact again.",
